{
  "stem": "2684.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Look, we had radio, and we had what you would call-- what we call the Voice of America, which you only could listen in a very, very quiet manner, because if some, somebody heard that you were listening, you were prosecuted.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And prosec-- by prosecution, I don't know what I mean.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know whether they'd been taken away or they'd been fined.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was too young to know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I knew, because I know from London even the, the, the signal of the station, the [SINGING] And when this came, we knew that we listening something which we are not supposed to listen.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it came through the Hungarian section of the London BBC.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we knew what happening around as much as you could hear on the radio.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, newspapers was fascist newspapers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I mean, it was Hungarian papers, which was governed by, those days, government.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they put into the paper whatever they want you to, to know and not what actually happened.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You didn't hear much about deportation, concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "All we heard is that, as I mentioned to you before, that young children came to our home to eat whose parents had been taken away, nobody knew where.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because when I, I was picked up and I was taken to Auschwitz, I didn't know where I was either.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "All I see on the lager, the head [INAUDIBLE] is 'Arbeit-- arbeit-- Arbeit macht frei.' And with my little knowledge, I know that 'works make you free.' And that was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was a slogan which stayed with me for the rest of my life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I tell you frankly, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even if I remember, I didn't give too much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't put too much attention, because I was a child.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
